{
  "texts": [
    "Conditions: Conditions in cybersecurity exercises include a set of tools that are linked to Virtual Machines (VMs) and used to monitor their status.",
    "Installed during feature setup, they report a status value ranging from 0 to 1, which is used for scoring and triggering events.",
    "Each condition has a unique name and requires either a periodic command or a defined source.",
    "When completely stated, the command and execution frequency take precedence over the source.",
    "Conditions can also include environment variablesfoot_1.-Command: This command provides the file path to the executable and yields a floatingpoint value ranging from 0 to 1."
  ]
}